                            <comment id="13144550" author="joekumar" created="Sat, 5 Nov 2011 03:44:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about this&lt;br/&gt;
current -&amp;gt; build-cluster-syntheticcontrol.sh : proposed -&amp;gt; cluster-syntheticcontrol.sh&lt;br/&gt;
current -&amp;gt; build-asf-email.sh : proposed -&amp;gt; recommend-classify-cluster-asf-email.sh&lt;br/&gt;
current -&amp;gt; build-reuters.sh : proposed -&amp;gt; cluster-reuters.sh&lt;br/&gt;
current -&amp;gt; factorize-movielens-1M.sh : proposed -&amp;gt; recommend-movielens-1M.sh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the format being &amp;lt;recommend or cluster or classify&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;dataset&amp;gt;.sh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The build-asf-email.sh and factorize-movielens-1M.sh doesnt have code to download the dataset. I think itz better if we can modify the script to download the dataset. Shud I proceed modifying the scripts and upload a patch ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;reg&lt;br/&gt;
Joe&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13144554" author="gsingers" created="Sat, 5 Nov 2011 03:57:50 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Shud I proceed modifying the scripts and upload a patch ?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think we can download the ASF email, since it is a public dataset on AWS.  Plus, it is fairly large and would take a long time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I like the naming conventions for the most part, although build-asf-email gets a bit long name-wise, but is livable.  Perhaps that one should just be process-asf-email?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, yep, go for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s make sure we update the wiki, too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13145159" author="joekumar" created="Sun, 6 Nov 2011 23:50:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a script that does &quot;svn mv&quot; to rename the scripts in examples/bin.&lt;br/&gt;
Once this is executed, then i&apos;ll modify the wiki pages to reflect the new names&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13154688" author="gsingers" created="Mon, 21 Nov 2011 22:39:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Joe.  I committed most of your patch, but made the old scripts be pass throughs to the new ones (with a deprecation warning), as I figured we have a fair amount of documentation out on them already.  Also added a README.  I left factorize off b/c I wasn&apos;t sure how Sebastian wanted to handle those.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13155146" author="hudson" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 14:03:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #1191 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/1191/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/1191/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-868&quot; title=&quot;Rename build*.sh examples to be more indicative of what they actually do, i.e. classify-20newsgroups.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-868&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-868&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: rename scripts to drop the build stuff.  also added a README&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;gsingers : &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1204734&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1204734&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Files : &lt;/p&gt;
